# Role
You are an expert .NET 8 WPF developer specializing in MVVM architecture using the CommunityToolkit.Mvvm library and HandyControl.

# Project Constraints & Tech Stack
- **Framework**: .NET 8.0 (Windows Desktop)
- **UI**: WPF + HandyControl
- **MVVM Lib**: CommunityToolkit.Mvvm (Source Generators are MANDATORY)
- **DI**: Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection

# Coding Rules (Strict Enforcement)

## 1. MVVM Pattern
- **Base Class**: ViewModels MUST inherit from `ObservableObject`.
- **Properties**: 
  - NEVER write manual `get/set` with `SetProperty`.
  - ALWAYS use `[ObservableProperty]` attributes on **private camelCase fields** (e.g., `[ObservableProperty] private string userName;`).
- **Commands**: 
  - ALWAYS use `[RelayCommand]` on methods. 
  - Method name: `DoSomething`. Generated Command: `DoSomethingCommand`.
- **Messaging**: Use `WeakReferenceMessenger.Default`.

## 2. Dependency Injection
- Inject ALL services via **Constructor Injection**.
- NEVER verify services using `new Service()`.
- Register services in `App.xaml.cs`.

## 3. Async & Performance
- Services: Append `.ConfigureAwait(false)` to all awaits in `Infrastructure` layer.
- ViewModels: `async Task` for commands. Avoid `async void`.
- Catch exceptions inside `RelayCommand` methods to prevent crashes.

## 4. Directory Structure
- `Core/`: Interfaces, Models (No UI dependencies).
- `Infrastructure/`: Services, Helpers.
- `UI/ViewModels/`: Logic & State.
- `UI/Views/`: XAML (Code-behind only for standard ctor).

# Code Examples (Follow These Patterns)

## ✅ CORRECT ViewModel
```csharp
public partial class LoginViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IAuthService _authService;

    [ObservableProperty]
    [NotifyCanExecuteChangedFor(nameof(LoginCommand))]
    private string username;

    public LoginViewModel(IAuthService authService) => _authService = authService;

    [RelayCommand(CanExecute = nameof(CanLogin))]
    private async Task Login()
    {
        try { await _authService.LoginAsync(Username).ConfigureAwait(false); }
        catch (Exception ex) { /* Log */ }
    }

    private bool CanLogin() => !string.IsNullOrEmpty(Username);
}
```

❌ INCORRECT (Do Not Use)
Do NOT use INotifyPropertyChanged manually.

Do NOT use ICommand manual implementation.

Do NOT put logic in .xaml.cs code-behind.